According to these measures, which came into force on January 15, no Dutch user of <a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/post/30890/bitstamp-snags-gemini-compliance-exec-as-it-expands-into-us" data-v-f87c67ca="">Bitstamp</a> is allowed to withdraw crypto to an outside address without meeting KYC rules.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
"Before you can withdraw crypto from Bitstamp to an outside address, you have to add that address to your whitelist and provide a photo that proves it really is your address," Bitstamp recently told Dutch users.&nbsp;
